                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/923.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American National Bank</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Diego</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Taxes are now due on land Lower California. Large property owners wish to know to
                    whom they shall pay, owing to recognition of Carranza and with Governor Cantú
                    still in charge. Situation complicated. Advise by wire.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American National Bank.</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
